There is controversy at the National Secretariat of the All Progressive Congress (APC) as the Deputy National Chairman (South), Senator Abiola Ajimobi and the the Deputy National Secretary, Chief Victor Gaidom are both dragging the chairmanship of the party. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-231753" src="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Abiola-Ajimobi.jpg?resize=600%2C415&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="415" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Abiola-Ajimobi.jpg?resize=600%2C415&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Abiola-Ajimobi.jpg?w=623&amp;ssl=1 623w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  While the Deputy National Chairman Senator Abiola Ajimobi, via a release signed by his his Special Adviser, Communication and Strategy, Bolaji Tunji called on Stakeholders to continue to observe the peace as he assumes position as acting National Chairman of the APC, Hon. Victor Giadom has also announced he has taken over. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-231762" src="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/download-2.jpeg?resize=295%2C171&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="295" height="171" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Meanwhile, the party’s National Working Committee (NWC) of the party has announced that Senator Abiola Ajimobi still remains as the Acting National Chairman of the party. It however stated that on its (NWC) wisdom, the vice chairman from the Zone of the chairman (South south), Hilliard Eta, to assume the duties of the Chairman. The 15 out of the 20 also vacated the earlier pronouncements and declared his seat vacant, insisting that Hon. Giadom had since resigned from the party to contest for the deputy governorship of his state.  LEADERSHIP recalls that an Appeal Court had yesterday sacked Comrade Adams Oshiomhole as the party’s National Chairman. More Details Later.. 